This paper deals with a communication network and its security, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The use of game theory to model the interactions between the different players suggests that it could also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. The presence of an eavesdropper and the focus on secrecy rates suggest that it could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. The use of a relay and the potential for interference suggests that it could also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Finally, the use of a relay to assist the eavesdropper and decrease the achievable secrecy rates suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
